It follows their fourth round of IVF. The couple, who have been together four years, started their fertility treatment in 2019. Adams, 39, the first woman to win a boxing Olympic gold medal, said: "It feels really good to finally have a baby on the way. All the ups and downs were worth it in the end." Baig, 24, who suffered a miscarriage after their first round of IVF, said: "I hope our story gives hope to other couples who might be in our position."